I was in Rockford with my boyfriend who was attending a fund raising event. While he was at his event I was searching on Google maps where to grab breakfast. I wandered to a few spots but each were not what I expected. Finally I found Sisters Cafe and was so happy with my experience. My server, Danielle was so sweet and attentive. My meal was perfect. I travel quite often and eat out a lot. I would have to say that my meal was perfect. My eggs were done right for a change. It's rare to get over-medium eggs. My one pancake was big and fluffy. It filled the entire plate! But for bacon lovers out there.... My bacon was absolutely perfect! It was the right crispyness and not over done. You will not be disappointed. I made sure to ask Danielle to let the chef know I was happy with my meal! If you're ever wondering where to have a great meal at a very reasonable price, look no further than Sisters Cafe off Chestnut and S Main.

Coffee came right away. It was hot but nothing special. Food came quicjly, was hot and fresh. I had chorizo skillet with eggs over easy and wheat toast. Hash browns were very good in skillet. Jalepenos were pickled, served in a small cup on the side.  Over easy eggs were perfect. Wife had three Swedish pancakes and said they were good. Half dozen more customers came in while we were there. Will definitely go back.
